block content
  .row.page-header(style="margin-bottom: 20px;")
    .col-lg-12
      h1(style="margin-top: 20px;") Munnar

  .row
    .col-xs-12.col-md-9
      .row
        .col-xs-14.col-sm-16
          h2(style="font-size: 24px;") Munnar
          p.rating
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-star
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-star
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-star
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-star-empty
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-star-empty
          p South-Indian, Land of nature
          .panel.panel-primary
            .panel-heading
              h2.panel-title About Munnar
            .panel-body
              p Munnar, located in the Idukki district of Kerala, is famous for its tea plantations, rolling hills, and cool climate. This hill station is surrounded by mist-covered mountains, and it's a popular destination for trekking, sightseeing, and relaxation.
              p Attractions include Eravikulam National Park, Anamudi Peak, and the tea estates that cover the region, offering visitors a chance to explore lush greenery and exotic wildlife.

          // Add images of Munnar here
          .row.images
            .col-xs-12
              h3(style="font-size: 24px;") Pothamedu Viewpoint
              img(src='/images/Pothamedu-Viewpoint.jpg', alt='Pothamedu Viewpoint', style='width:100%; height:auto;')
              p(style="font-size: 18px;") Pothamedu Viewpoint offers panoramic views of the lush green valleys, tea plantations, and hills. This secluded spot is perfect for a peaceful retreat, away from the crowds.

            .col-xs-12
              h3(style="font-size: 24px;") Lockhart Gap
              img(src='/images/lock hart gap.jpg', alt='Lock Hart Gap', style='width:100%; height:auto;')
              p(style="font-size: 18px;") Lockhart Gap is known for its captivating landscapes and serene ambiance. Visitors can enjoy breathtaking views of the mountains and valleys, making it a perfect spot for nature lovers.

            // New image 1
            .col-xs-12
              h3(style="font-size: 24px;") Anayirangal Dam
              img(src='/images/Anayirangal-Dam.jpg', alt='Anayirangal Dam', style='width:100%; height:auto;')
              p(style="font-size: 18px;") Anayirangal Dam is surrounded by tea plantations and offers a scenic view of the reservoir and nearby hills. It's a peaceful place to relax and enjoy nature.

            // New image 2
            .col-xs-12
              h3(style="font-size: 24px;") Attukal Waterfalls
              img(src='/images/Attukal-Waterfalls.jpg', alt='Attukal Waterfalls', style='width:100%; height:auto;')
              p(style="font-size: 18px;") Attukal Waterfalls is a beautiful cascade set amidst lush greenery. It's an ideal spot for trekking and enjoying the fresh mountain air.

            // New image 3
            .col-xs-12
              h3(style="font-size: 24px;") Top Station
              img(src='/images/topstations.jpg', alt='Top Station', style='width:100%; height:auto;')
              p(style="font-size: 18px;") Top Station, located on the Kerala-Tamil Nadu border, offers breathtaking views of the Western Ghats. It's a popular destination for visitors who enjoy panoramic vistas.

            // New image 4
            .col-xs-12
              h3(style="font-size: 24px;") Lakkom Waterfalls
              img(src='/images/Lakkom-Waterfalls.jpg', alt='Lakkom Waterfalls', style='width:100%; height:auto;')
              p(style="font-size: 18px;") Lakkom Waterfalls is a stunning waterfall located in a picturesque setting. The falls are surrounded by tea estates, making it a favorite spot for visitors to relax and enjoy the scenery.

